# Key History UI Plan

## Goal Description
Display a running log of the detected piano keys on the Streamlit web interface so the user can see what they have played.

## User Review Required
None.

## Proposed Changes
### files
#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/app.py)
- **UI Element**: Add a `st.empty()` container below the video or in a sidebar to hold the history.
- **State**: Initialize a `history` list (empty).
- **Update Logic**:
    - Inside the detection loop, when a key is pressed (and printed to console), append it to the `history` list.
    - Keep only the last ~20 items to prevent it from growing indefinitely.
    - Update the `st.empty()` container with the formatted string of keys (e.g., "C D E F G").

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- Run the app.
- Press keys.
- Verify they appear in the UI list.
